The Syntax for fetching of a raw repo'd file currently is suffixing a browsed URL with '?raw':

{noformat}
http://host/projects/{project}/repos/{repo}/browse/path/to/file.ext?raw
{noformat}

It would be helpful if an (additional?) URL syntax could be provided which preserved path/to/file.ext as the end of the URL, such that files can not only be referenced over HTTP, but relative paths within those files will naturally resolve under the URL syntax.  An example:

{noformat}
http://host/projects/{project}/repos/{repo}/raw/path/to/file.ext
{noformat}

As a customer, I want to be able to configure Stash to trigger a Fisheye scan request after a commit using a plugin. Currently you can use a [REST API|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/FISHEYE/Configuring+commit+hooks] to do that. However it requires the API key sent as HTTP header ("X-Api-Key: xxx").


{panel}
Currently you can do that using the [Fisheye post-receive hook for Stash|https://bitbucket.org/jschumacher/fisheye-post-receive-hook-for-stash/downloads]. However this plugin is not fully supported and this issue is here as a task to release this plugin in the Marketplace.

You can upload the .jar file via the Plugin Manager in the global administration of Stash. Once you've done that, a hook will be available in each repository, allowing you to notify FishEye of any new commits to Stash.
{panel}

